f=Cybersecurity/warden/operational/tool/warden-tool-requirements.md · h1:warden — Tool Requirements=**Specifies needs; grant them.** Access configured deployment (Fleet Charter Rails 1–2 registered tools, least privilege). external call plan-locked (Eng Rail sandboxed (Rail 2). · h1:warden — Tool Requirements=\| Skill \| Needs \| Why \| · h1:warden — Tool Requirements=\|---\|---\|---\| · h1:warden — Tool Requirements=\| security-policy-framework \| GRC pack (runtime-install, Sushegaad, MIT); file read/write (own ISMS/policy index) \| control catalog + mapping \| · h1:warden — Tool Requirements=\| risk-register \| script execution (risk_score.py — stdlib); file read/write (own append-only register) \| scored, tracked risks \| · h1:warden — Tool Requirements=\| third-party-risk \| file read/write (own vendor register); read of vendor certs/questionnaires \| vendor assessment \| · h1:warden — Tool Requirements=\| security-exception-process \| file read/write (own append-only exception register) \| time-boxed waivers \| · h2:Explicit non-needs hard prohibition (the security-inversion)=**NO keys, credentials, privileged access.** warden never provisions, contains, remediates operator executes privileged change., **No write access production systems, cloud accounts, identity stores** warden writes policy risk records only., **No risk acceptance authority material risk** that's operator's/board's. · n=warden department's most-watched, least-privileged agent design; power analysis policy, action., GRC pack runtime-installed connector (rank/claude-seo pattern), surfaced operator chosen standard.